## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of online resources and the potential bias in historical interpretations. Some sources may present a Eurocentric view, underrepresenting the impact of Japanese militarism in Asia. Additionally, the complexity of international relations in the interwar period means that not all contributing factors to World War II can be fully explored in this brief report.

